// ============================================================
// THE DIGITAL INCOME EDIT™ — MASTER ARTICLE LAYOUT
// Every article page wraps its content in this layout.
// To publish a new article: create a new file in
// src/pages/learn/ using this same layout, keep the frontmatter
// fields, and write the article body as the page content.
// Nothing here needs to change per-article.
//
// STRUCTURED DATA
// Article schema emits on every page, generated from props.
//
// ⚠️ datePublished is OPTIONAL here so that pages which don't
// pass it still build. It is omitted from the schema when
// absent rather than emitted empty or faked. This is a
// deliberate, temporary state: Google's Article spec lists
// datePublished as REQUIRED, and pages without it will be
// flagged in Search Console and lose article rich-result
// eligibility. Backfill the twelve dates and pass them here.
// No layout change is needed when you do.
//
// FAQPage schema emits only when the optional `faqs` prop is
// passed. Answers passed to `faqs` MUST match the visible FAQ
// text in the article body verbatim — Google penalises
// structured data that isn't present in the rendered page.
//
// ============================================================
// NOTE ON MULTI-ELEMENT CONDITIONAL BRANCHES
// ============================================================
// Do NOT use `<>...</>` shorthand — Astro does not support it.
// Do NOT use `<Fragment>` without importing it from 'astro/jsx-runtime'
// — an unimported capitalized tag is parsed as raw markup, the
// enclosing block's structure breaks, and the compiler reports an
// orphaned closing tag SOMEWHERE DOWNSTREAM of the real cause.
// Both mistakes were made in this file and both produced the same
// misleading "Closing tag '</a>' has no matching opening tag" error
// pointing at the newsletter section, which was never broken.
//
// Where a conditional branch needs to render more than one element,
// wrap it in a real element (see the affiliate block below). Simpler,
// no import, nothing to forget.
//
// ============================================================
// PER-PILLAR ROUTING — Resource Map v2.0, Part 2
// ============================================================
// The journey block below is NO LONGER HARDCODED. It reads
// `category` and routes to that pillar's row.
//
// THE OMISSION RULE (the reason most rows look empty):
// Resource Map v2.0, Part 4 records that ONE of twelve
// free-resource routes and ONE of twelve paid-resource routes
// exist on the live site. Every other route on the map is
// marked "does not exist."
//
// A slot is populated here ONLY if its destination is a live
// page. Where it is not, the slot is OMITTED ENTIRELY and the
// article renders newsletter +
